    <section id="story">
        <span class="section-label">The Mystery</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Behind the Crimson Drapes</h2>
        
        <div class="story-grid">
            <div class="story-left">
                <blockquote class="story-highlight-quote">
                    "Think of the content, babe. Ghosts? Algorithms love ghosts!" [cite: 40]
                </blockquote>
                <div class="story-summary">
                    <p>What happens when a brand-conscious, social-media-influencing wife drags her cynical, allergy-ridden husband to a colonial-era bungalow that boasts a dirt-cheap room rate along with complimentary poltergeists? [cite: 8, 10, 16, 18, 32] <strong>The Honeymoon Haunting</strong> follows newlyweds Priya and Rahul as their romantic getaway transforms into a chaotic, laughter-filled nightmare[cite: 7, 35, 133].</p>
                    <p>Instead of serene beaches, they find themselves sharing a bedroom with Shyam, a floating, stylish ghost who wears Ray-Bans and possesses a sharp wit[cite: 64, 65, 128]. As the lines between two separate narratives within the estate blur—shifting between Rahul & Priya's ghost-hunting exploits and Mira & Arjun's entanglement in structural resort curses [cite: 753, 758, 796]—the novel serves up an eccentric blend of modern digital obsession, classic gothic tropes, and accidental matchmaking beyond the grave[cite: 10, 351, 388].</p>
                </div>
                <div class="theme-tags">
                    <span class="theme-tag">Paranormal Comedy</span>
                    <span class="theme-tag">Romantic Satire</span>
                    <span class="theme-tag">Social Media Satire</span>
                    <span class="theme-tag">Indian Gothic-ish</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="stats-sidebar">
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-number">13</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Chapters</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
