    <section id="characters">
        <span class="section-label">Dramatis Personae</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">The Living & The Departed</h2>
        
        <div class="characters-container">
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="character-header">
                    <h3 class="character-name">Priya</h3>
                    <span class="character-role">Main Character / Influencer Wife</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-body">
                    <p>A brand-conscious Instagram influencer who documents every blinking moment of her life[cite: 8, 10]. She is thrilled by the promotional aspect of staying at a haunted colonial mansion[cite: 16, 40].</p>
                    <div class="character-traits">
                        <span class="trait-chip">Enthusiastic</span>
                        <span class="trait-chip">Content-Driven</span>
                        <span class="trait-chip">Fearless</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="character-header">
                    <h3 class="character-name">Rahul</h3>
                    <span class="character-role">Main Character / Skeptical Husband</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-body">
                    <p>Priya's long-suffering, allergy-ridden husband[cite: 9, 32]. He values silence, hates appearing in couple reels, and would significantly prefer a normal, ghost-free trip to Goa[cite: 9, 17].</p>
                    <div class="character-traits">
                        <span class="trait-chip">Sarcastic</span>
                        <span class="trait-chip">Anxious</span>
                        <span class="trait-chip">Reluctant Hero</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="character-header">
                    <h3 class="character-name">Shyam</h3>
                    <span class="character-role">Spectral Roommate</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-body">
                    <p>A dashing, transparent ghost floating two inches off the ground[cite: 64]. He stalks the corridors in a designer sherwani and Ray-Bans, bringing hospitality mixed with heavy sarcasm[cite: 64, 128, 134].</p>
                    <div class="character-traits">
                        <span class="trait-chip">Stylish</span>
                        <span class="trait-chip">Sarcastic</span>
                        <span class="trait-chip">Heartbroken</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="character-header">
                    <h3 class="character-name">Mira & Arjun</h3>
                    <span class="character-role">The Detective Couple</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-body">
                    <p>A secondary parallel honeymooning couple who inherit a subsequent layer of supernatural entanglements, culminating in ownership of the bizarre resort itself[cite: 753, 796, 835].</p>
                    <div class="character-traits">
                        <span class="trait-chip">Pros at Chaos</span>
                        <span class="trait-chip">Adaptive</span>
                        <span class="trait-chip">Entrepreneurs</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="chapters">
        <span class="section-label">Index of Misadventures</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">The Chronicles of Whispering Orchards</h2>
        
        <div class="chapters-grid">
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">01</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Perfect Couple... Almost</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Priya drags Rahul to a ridiculously cheap, historic mansion[cite: 7, 16]. The price tag includes free Wi-Fi... and unexpected architectural well-springs[cite: 20, 38].</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">02</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Room Service from the Other Side</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Hot samosas and streaming chai float straight into their quarters[cite: 104, 108, 131]. But the complimentary compliments on the mirror prove to be far less appetizing[cite: 119, 120].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">03</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Spirit with the Selfie Stick</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Shyam joins the marital landscape full-time, demanding closure for an old engagement ring mishap involving an aggressive mansion monkey[cite: 141, 147, 148, 186].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">04</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Whispering Walls and a Very Confused Electrician</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">A highly confused local electrician tries to resolve spiritual anomalies with grounding wire, while a toaster starts sending direct messages[cite: 241, 247, 255, 263].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">05</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Sherwani Shocker</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">A ghost-fiancée enters the fray, demanding a grand spiritual wedding and triggering a full-scale project management nightmare for the living[cite: 330, 350, 351, 388].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">06</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Unholy Matrimony</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Ancient ritual circles are drawn with questionable expired ghee, leading to a profound revelation within a dusty, charred diary of the dead[cite: 390, 419, 430, 434].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">07</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Secrets in the Suitcase</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">A hidden zipper reveals a dark letter from an old resident warning the couple that their beloved, stylish ghost may not be who he claims to be[cite: 466, 485, 494].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">08</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Spirit of Suspicion</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">A lanky academic arrives talking about local legends, prompting a midnight raid on a basement altar that implicates the grace of the house help[cite: 558, 588, 595, 606, 611].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">09</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Séance Shenanigans</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Equipped with an Ikea plate and a soup spoon, the crew uncovers a vintage bride ghost who replaced cosmetic facials with pure mustard[cite: 623, 626, 627, 634, 646, 662].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">10</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">A Killer Evening and a Confession to Die For</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">A different perspective takes form as things escalate into a cinematic thriller night featuring an unusually aggressive, wire-wrapped mop weapon[cite: 688, 744].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">11</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Séance Surprise</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Restless spirits and missing premium chocolate-covered almond baskets crash a Sanskrit performance, revealing bizarre truths about a mango pickle[cite: 752, 759, 763, 768].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">12</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Love, Laughter, and Leftover Ghosts</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Mira and Arjun assume formal management roles of a paranormally active piece of real estate, receiving structural deeds from the afterlife[cite: 795, 796, 831, 835].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-num">13</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Happily Ever After...ish</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Capitalism monetization meets ectoplasm. Bookings surge 300% as the narrative wraps up with a distinct, multi-lingual aviary threat[cite: 850, 863, 866, 899].</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

